===Transitive Verb 2===

====Etymology====
Old French [[aprouer]]; a (Latin ad) + a form apparently derived from the pro, prod, in Latin [[prodest]] it is useful or profitable, properly the preposition  pro for. Compare with [[Improve]].

====Definition====
#  (English Law) To make profit of; to convert to one's own profit;&mdash;said  esp. of waste or common land appropriated by the lord of the  manor.
